      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "combat",
          "intro": "The whole build ladder on one screen. For the Sidewinder there is barely a ladder — Initial is a fightable starter, A-Rated is as far as it's worth taking, and Engineered is shown only for completeness (don't actually grind materials for this hull). A-Rated swaps the starter pulse for a second multi-cannon and A-rates the power chain; Engineered applies the standard small-combat tour at trivial grade.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Reality check",
            "text": "This is the absolute ceiling of a Sidewinder combat fit, and it's still weaker than a stock Eagle. Build the Initial column, not the Engineered one — spend your materials on a hull that deserves them."
          },
          "notes": {
            "SmallHardpoint1": "Primary gimballed multi-cannon; Overcharged lifts the tiny DPS ceiling, Auto Loader keeps it firing through the fight.",
            "SmallHardpoint2": "Second multi-cannon (swapped in from the starter pulse); Overcharged + Corrosive Shell strips target armour resistance for the whole battery.",
            "TinyHardpoint1": "Shield booster; Heavy Duty is the cheapest large multiplier on a paper shield, Super Capacitors adds raw MJ.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds chaff salvos. Chaff spoils gimballed and turreted fire.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rate for headroom to run two guns and a shield; Overcharged adds power, Thermal Spread bleeds the extra heat.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rate + Dirty Drives for the agility a fragile hull lives or dies on; Drag Drives sharpens the boost.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "A-rate to reach your RES; Increased Range with Mass Manager — combat itself needs no jump range.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass; Lightweight trims more, and life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "A-rate this FIRST — the single biggest fix; Charge Enhanced + Super Conduits let the two guns fire longer before WEP empties.",
            "Radar": "D-rate and go Lightweight; combat needs no sensor range, so save the mass on a hull this light.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock tank; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size2": "Bi-weave regenerates fast between passes so the paper shield comes back; Reinforced + Hi-Cap maximise its MJ.",
            "Slot02_Size2": "Hull reinforcement; Heavy Duty + Deep Plating is the cheapest large gain in effective armour.",
            "Slot03_Size1": "Second hull reinforcement fills the next slot for a little more survivability.",
            "Slot04_Size1": "Module Reinforcement spreads penetrating-hit damage across the cores; not engineerable."
          },
